INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('12', 'LD3-SE', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Introduction</SPAN>\r\nThe Little Dot LD III SE uses the NOS Telefunken EL152 antique tubes as power output tubes; for pre-amplification, it uses the Western Electric WE408A . These tubes are now legendary “artifact”, and we only have 150 sets of new NOS inventory, so the machine is a true “limited edition.”\r\n\r\nThe machine uses a specially designed Z11 core output transformer, coupling capacitor uses Mundorf silver oil capacitors, and resistors are Kiwame for AUDIO-specific resistors. Teflon silver wire is used within the machine, and the German silver solder. Headphone output section, using our developed “intelligent recognition impedance” proprietary technology that can automatically detect impedance headphones, and switch to the appropriate interface.\r\n\r\nTelefunken EL152 output power (larger than the famous 300B); sound excellent, with so much musical detail. Such tubes are antique collection!\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Reviews</SPAN>\r\n<A HREF=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZbZs2BoX39k\" target=\"_blank\">These are Limited Version for a Reason ! Little Dot LD3SE tube integrated amplifier review by Jay\'s iyagi @ Youtube</A>\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Parameters</SPAN>\r\n• Input terminals:\r\n	RCA x2\r\n• Output terminal :\r\n	1,6.35 x1 (headphone output)\r\n	2, RCA x2 (Pre Out)\r\n• Distortion: 0.1% (1000Hz)\r\n• Signal to Noise Ratio: 96dB\r\n• Frequency response:\r\n	1,20Hz – 20KHz (-1dB)\r\n	2,20Hz – 40KHz (-2dB)\r\n• Output power:\r\n	Maximum output power: 10W + 10W\r\n• Rated output power:\r\n	10W (8 Ω)\r\n	6W (32 Ω)\r\n	2W (300 Ω)\r\n• Magnification:\r\n	GAIN = HIGH: 10\r\n	GAIN = LOW: 5\r\n• Power consumption: 120 VA\r\n• Size: 230x250x140(h)mm\r\n• Weight: 8Kg ((With separate power adapter))', '4', '1', 'All tubes headphone & speak amp', '0000000111', '2008-08-08', '1');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('13', 'LD-X1', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Description</SPAN>\r\nLD X1 is the current flagship solid state amplifier from Little Dot. This amp was designed to drive most of the flagship headphone. Not only it has a lot of power, but it is very detail at the same time. It drives both high or low-impendence dynamic headphone, and it also drives planar headphones perfectly as well.\r\n\r\nLD X1 uses discrete component design in order to achieve the highest standard both on charts and actual listening experience, and this is something that an integrated circuit design would be having difficulties to reach such a standard. Also, due to the working state cannot be changed on an integrated circuit design, it cannot be an actual “pure class-A” amplifier.\r\n\r\nThe components, including Kendeil, Vishay, ELNA and SILMIC II silk capacitors, were carefully chosen for maximum synergy; delivering purity of sound, bombastic dynamics, silky details, and three dimensional sound-stage imaging.\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Parameters</SPAN>\r\n• Inputs: \r\n	(1) 3-pin XLR\r\n	(2) RCA\r\n• Outputs: \r\n	(1) 4-pin XLR headphone output\r\n	(2) 6.35mm TRS headphone output\r\n	(3) 3-pin XLR headphone/pre-amp output\r\n• Total Distortion: 0.001% (2V rms @ 1000Hz)\r\n• Signal to Noise: 98dB\r\n• Frequency Response: 5 Hz – 100 KHz (-3dB), 10 Hz – 50 KHz (-1dB)\r\n• Output Power: 6W per channel @ 32 Ω, 1W per channel @ 300 Ω\r\n• Gain Settings: High (5x) and Low (3x)\r\n• Power Consumption: 60 VA\r\n', '3', '3', 'The flagship Solid State headphone amplifier', '0000000122', '2008-08-08', '1');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('14', 'MK6+', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Description</SPAN>\r\nThe Little Dot MK VI+ is one of our best-selling headphone amplifier/pre-amplifier in the Little Dot MK-series. A fully balanced design, the Little Dot MK VI+ has exceptional dynamic range and can produce clean amplitudes of 70Vp-p into 120 ohms! The balanced Class-A SEPP (single-ended push pull) OCL (output capacitor-less) circuit topology delivers rich tonality and powerful force for maximum dynamics and low frequency impact. Also, MK VI+ provides the upgrade version and it saves you a lot of work to modify the machine, and upgrade pre-amp tubes is also available upon request\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">SPECIFICATIONS</SPAN>\r\n• Available in either Black (default) or Silver\r\n• Fully Balanced Architecture\r\n• SEPP (Single-ended Push Pull) OCL (Output CapacitorLess) in Class-A\r\n• Active 2 fan cooling\r\n• Driver Tubes: 2x 6H9C\r\n• Power Tubes: 4x 6080WC\r\n• Inputs:\r\n	Balanced: 2x 3-pin XLR\r\n	Single-ended: 2x RCA\r\n• Outputs:\r\n	Balanced: 4-Pin XLR\r\n	Balanced Pre-Amp: 2x 3-pin XLR\r\n• Single-ended: 1/4″ (6.35mm) TRS Stereo jack\r\n• Frequency Response:Input Impedance: 50K Ω\r\n	5Hz – 80KHz (-3dB)\r\n	10Hz – 30KHz (-1dB)\r\n• Pre-Amplifier Output Impedance: 600 Ω\r\n• THD+N:Power Output:\r\n	0.02% (2Vrms @ 1000Hz)\r\n	0.06% (10Vrms @ 1000Hz)\r\n	0.3% (20Vrms @ 1000Hz)\r\n• Output Power: 5W per channel in 120 Ω\r\n• Power Consumption: 25 VA\r\n• Size: 350x290x140(h)mm\r\n• Weight: 9.6KG(about 21.15 pounds)\r\n• One Year Official Little Dot Warranty\r\n\r\nUpgrade version includes:\r\n• 4 Mundorf MCap SUPREME Silver Oil as coupling capacitors\r\n• Silver plated teflon wiring\r\n• WBT Silver solder on the signal nodes\r\n• Pre-amp tubes: Mullard CV4024 (optional, and socket convertor would be included)', '1', '1', ' •Fully Balanced Circuit<BR>\r\n•Use as pre-amp', '0000000222', '2008-08-08', '4');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('15', 'MK8-SE', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Description</SPAN>\r\nThe Little Dot MK 8 SE further specializes our Little Dot MK 6 platform for no-compromise performance with high impedance headphones. Fully balanced design with single-ended headphone functionality as well, the Little Dot MK VIII SE is also dual-mono with independent amplifiers with their own isolated toroidal transformer power supplies. An output capacitor-less design minimizes components in the signal path, delivering a “pure” signal free from unwanted distortion and color. The Little Dot MK VIII SE’s sound signature is designed to be provide a reference-level of transparency with a touch of tube warmth and tonal richness.\r\n\r\nKey Point:\r\n• All the balanced socket on the machine is reliable NIUTRIK™,Swiss XLR socket.\r\n• Volume control potentiometer from ALPS™,Japan.\r\n• Resistance from DALE™,USA. Capacitance from WIMA™/ERO™/CHEMI-COM™, Germany.\r\n• Ample sound field, high accuracy, excellent gradations, and nice control ability.\r\n• Both working as headphone amplifier and balanced pre-amplifier.\r\n• Gold award winner of 1st Hong Kong “Headphone Amplifier King”.  \r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">SPECIFICATIONS</SPAN>\r\n• Available in either Black  or Silver\r\n• Fully Balanced, Dual-Mono Architecture\r\n• Inputs:\r\n	Balanced: 2x 3-pin XLR\r\n	Single-ended: 2x RCA\r\n• Outputs:\r\n	Balanced: 4-Pin XLR\r\n	Balanced Pre-Amp: 2x 3-pin XLR\r\n	Single-ended: 1/4″ (6.35mm) TRS Stereo jack\r\n• Input Impedance: 50K  Ω\r\n• Frequency Response:\r\n	5Hz – 80KHz (-3dB)\r\n	10Hz – 30KHz (-1dB)\r\n• Pre-Amplifier Output Impedance: 600  Ω\r\n• THD+N:Signal-to-Noise: \r\n	96 dB0.01% (2Vrms @ 1000Hz)\r\n	0.03% (10Vrms @ 1000Hz)\r\n	0.2% (20Vrms @ 1000Hz)\r\n• Voltage Swing: 60V p-p\r\n• Power Output:\r\n	2W per channel @ 600 Ω\r\n	1W per channel @ 300 Ω\r\n• Power Consumption: 100 VA\r\n• Size: 350x290x140(h)mm\r\n• Weight: 9.6KG(about 21.15 pounds)\r\n\r\nUpgrade version includes:\r\n• 4 Mundorf MCap SUPREME Silver Oil as coupling capacitors\r\n• Silver plated teflon wiring\r\n• WBT Silver solder on the signal nodes\r\n• Pre-amp tubes: Mullard CV4024 (optional)', '1', '1', '•Fully Balanced Circuit<BR>\r\n•Use as pre-amp', '0000000133', '2008-08-08', '5');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('16', 'MK3+', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Introduction</SPAN>\r\nMK3+ used a combined framework. The tube front stage presents sweet sound performance and transistor back stage supports high drive power. This framework guaranteed both high-current to drive low resistance headphones and high voltage swing for high resistance headphones.\r\nThe tube parts of MK3+ is set up with a pair of 6C4 tubes.Transistor parts is a PNP/NPN discrete symmetrical Class-A amplifier circuit.\r\n\r\nCombined framework keeps advantages form both tube and transistor. Especially it performs excellently when driving low resistance headphones. \r\n\r\nMK3+ has two versions: with Bluetooth wireless input or not. The Bluetooth Version has a v4.2 Bluetooth module for good wireless utility.\r\n\r\nOxidation treated surface and golden plated tube guard board.\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Parameters</SPAN>\r\n• Input ports: RCA*2\r\n• Output ports: 6.35mm(1/4inch)*1, (Pre-Amplifier)RCA*2 \r\n• Input resistance: 10Kohm\r\n• THD: 0.001%  2V@RMS 1000Hz\r\n• SNR: 95dB\r\n• Frequency Response: 5Hz --- 100KHz(-1dB)\r\n• Output power: 2.5W@32ohm\r\n	1.8W@120Ω\r\n	0.8W@300Ω\r\n• Adapt headphone resistance: 32Ω ~ 600Ω\r\n• Magnification: 9@GAIN=HIGH, 4.5@GAIN=LOW\r\n• Power consumption: 25VA\r\n• Size: 245x165x120(H)mm\r\n• Weight: 3Kg\r\n\r\n', '2', '1', 'Hybrid tube', '0000000111', '2008-08-08', '3');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('17', 'MK9', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Introduction</SPAN>\r\nLittle Dot MK9 uses 3 tubes; the pre-amp tube: 6N9P, and the power-amp tubes: 6080*2. The input signal is the audio signal from the CD player or DAC, an amplified output signal used to drive headphones. You can also use the MK 9 as pre-amp, just use its RCA connection to connect a power amp.\r\n\r\nThe circuit output dynamic than the cathode output generally large (undistorted swing: 30Vp-p), due to the cancellation of the output capacitance, low frequency response can dive deeper and it provides solid bass, and mid can be more transparent.\r\n\r\nBut in order to make the circuit in the case of direct coupled DC level is zero, need symmetrical supply complex. In order to stabilize the operation of the circuit, and the machine also adopts a “zero servo tracking circuit”. In order to ensure the safety of the output load, relay protection circuit and output protection special chip.\r\n\r\nThe machine output tube uses a new production of the RCA company 50 years antique tube (NOS), is one of the best tubes in the world.\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Parameters</SPAN>\r\n•  Input terminal: RCA\r\n•  Output terminal:RCA (pre amplifier with); 6.35 earphone socket.\r\n•  Frequency response: 12HZ—100KHZ (-1dB)\r\n•  Distortion: 0.05% (300Ω, 80 mW)\r\n•  The maximum output power of :A. 300 mw (600/300Ω);B. 350 mw (120Ω);C. 250 MW (32Ω)\r\n•  Output impedance: 32 ohm – 600 ohm\r\n•  Voltage: 110V or 220V (user specified)\r\n•  Power consumption: 80 VA\r\n• Size: 300 (D) X220 (W) X150 (H) mm\r\n• Weight: 4 Kg\r\n', '1', null, '•High-current output<BR>\r\n•Use as pre-amp', '0000000011', '2008-08-08', '3');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('18', 'MINI4', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Introduction</SPAN>\r\nLittleDot Mini-4 Music Center contains 4 devices:\r\n1•  DP-4 Stream Media Player\r\nBase on Raspberry Pi 4B, DP-4 has a Quad Core 1.5Ghz 64bit ARM Cortex-A72 CPU. This powerful processor makes DP-4 readily processes all kinds HQ audio data. DP-4 has a AK4137 SRC module for PCM - DSD format conversion. The low jitter clock recovery circuit ensured clock working on a high stable condition during stream playing.\r\nDP-4 supports USB device like Flash Disk and portable hard-drive. Otherwise, DP-4 has powerful wireless function for Bluetooth, LAN, DLAN, Air-Play etc.\r\n<HR>\r\n2• DA-4 Digital Decoder\r\nDecoder scheme is on AK4493 DAC, PCM support is up to 768KHz/32bit, and DSD up to 256Bit. This DAC chip is a new product belong to AKM VELVET SOUND series. By the OSRD(over sampling rate doubly) tech, AK4493 can substantially reduce interference noise support the player more clear sound performance.\r\n<HR>\r\n3• AM-4 Headphone Amplifier\r\nAM-4 is designed with entire discrete symmetrical Class-A circuit without any molectron. This circuit has better Instantaneous response speed and lower crossover distortion.\r\n<HR>\r\n4• PO-4 Power Supply\r\nEven for a mini size music center, we added a linear power in the set. Compared to general switch power supply, linear power supply with high-power ring transformer can ensure a much stable driving power for the system.\r\n<HR>\r\nMini-4 is a set of mini size music center. But we set every module same as the full-size system. Complete sound performance and portable size, this is the most excellent advantage of this product.\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Accessories:</SPAN>\r\n• RJ45 network cable(for I²S connect)*1\r\n• 3-pin power cable*1 \r\n• Devices connect power cable*3\r\n• Main power cable(Aviation plug)*1\r\n• 3.5 to 3.5 resistance adaptor*1 (for low resistance headphones).\r\n• 3.5 to 6.35 adaptor*1\r\n', '5', '1', '4 in 1 Stream Music Center', '0000000111', '2008-08-08', '2');
INSERT INTO `products` VALUES ('19', 'D300', '<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Description</SPAN>\r\nThe full Littledot D300 set consists of two parts:\r\n1. D300 pre amplifier\r\n2. D300 power amplifier\r\nThe above two can be purchased separately, but we strongly suggest that you use it with our pre-amp.\r\n\r\nLittle Dot’s D300 mono block power amp is little, but it surely provides a lot of power!\r\n\r\nThe D300 preamplifier uses 6J1 vacuum tubes as the input amplifier. The voltage drive of the BUF makes the front stage not only have sufficient driving force, but also have a warm and sweet sound, which effectively improves the sound quality of the power amplifier.\r\n\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Specifications of D300 Pre Amp</SPAN>\r\n• THD+N: 0.01 % 1kHz, 2 V rms, 600Ω\r\n• SNR: 99 dB\r\n• Voltage gain: 1kHz 2.2 times\r\n• Frequency Response: 10 100kHz, 600Ω ±1 dB\r\n• ZIN: 100 kΩ\r\n• Volume: 300*175*70mm\r\n• Weight: 2.23 Kg\r\n<HR>\r\n<SPAN CLASS=\"title\">Specifications of D300 Power Amp</SPAN>\r\n• Rated output power: 20 20kHz, THD+N<0.1%, 4Ω 300W\r\n• THD+N: 0.03 % 1kHz, 50W, 8Ω\r\n• SNR: 98 dB\r\n• Voltage gain: 1 kHz 31 dB\r\n• Frequency Response: 20 20kHz, 8Ω ±1 dB\r\n• ZIN: 10 kΩ\r\n• Native efficiency: 200W @ 8Ω 91 %\r\n', '9', null, 'D-Class Digital Amplifier', '0000000111', '2017-08-08', '1');
